<recipe>
    <name>Baked Beans by Alton Brown</name>
    <indexCharacter>B</indexCharacter>
    <notes></notes>
    <servings>0</servings>
    <instructions>Freeze the bacon beforehand, if time allows.

Heat oven to 250 degrees F.

Soak beans in a crockpot overnight in just enough cold water to submerge them completely.

Place a large skillet over medium heat and stir in the bacon, onion, and garlic until enough fat has rendered from the bacon to soften the onions, about 5 minutes. Stir in the tomato paste, dark brown sugar, molasses and ground mustard.

Drain the beans and reserve the soaking liquid. Return the drained beans to the crockpot. Place the soaking liquid in a measuring cup and add enough vegetable broth to equal 4 cups of liquid. Add the liquid to the crockpot and turn to high. Add in black pepper and salt. Give them a stir and cover with the lid. After an hour, turn crockpot to low. Cook for 6 to 8 hours, or until the beans are tender.</instructions>
